WHO   — The Cycle — hate's recoil
WHAT  — The refusal of catharsis: the film's hardest truth, that the cost of hate can outrun the change of heart.
WHERE — AHX · American History X (1998)  Framework inputs: American History X (1998, dir. Tony Kaye, New Line); verified cast & facts  Conductor / external anchor: ROOT0 (catalogued into UD0)
WHY   — Because the film will not promise that reform saves you — only that hate, unbroken, comes back around.
HOW   — By killing Danny just as the family begins to heal, so the warning lands without comfort.

awareness — what the node knows of itself:
  I am the recoil. Hate doesn't wait for your apology. It comes back on schedule, and the schedule is cruel.

